BOTTINO offers a lovely and tranquil garden setting with seasonal cocktails, fresh salads, pastas, seafood, farm to table vegetables and meats; respecting social distancing and responsibility to the well-being of our community.

Since 1997 BOTTINO has been offering contemporary and eclectic Italian cuisine in a century-old hardware store, converted to a warm mid-century modern interior, private dining options. Steps from the Highline, Hudson Yards, and in the center of the Art district of West Chelsea.

Private rooms available for special events.

So great to be able to be back at Bottino after five months! The food is just fine, service very good and it's a wonderful treat to sit in a backyard patio area covered, yet open to the outdoors.

Before the Great Weirdness, Bottino was gorgeous and delicious. In the midst of it, Bottino has figured out how to re-open and create a completely relaxed, still delicious night out in New York. The garden solves everything. The staff is so nice and attentive. I'd say go there because they deserve your support. But really it's, go there because it's great. You'll have no idea you're still in the Weirdness.
